t-reject-not-accept\/","url_meta":{"origin":39789,"position":0},"title":"Hadith on Conscience: Whatever your heart rejects, do not accept it","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 1, 2016","format":false,"excerpt":"Abdur Rahman ibn Mu\u2019awiyah reported: A man asked the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, saying, \u201cO Messenger of Allah, what is lawful and unlawful for me?\u201d The Prophet struck his chest and he said, \u201cWhatever your heart rejects, abandon it.\u201d Source: al-Zuhd wal-Raqa\u0304\u2019iq 1147 Grade: Sahih\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":41873,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2024\/03\/28\/ibn-sireen-conscience\/","url_meta":{"origin":39789,"position":1},"title":"Ibn Sireen on Conscience: Allah makes his heart admonish him","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"March 28, 2024","format":false,"excerpt":"Habib reported: Ibn Sirin, may Allah have mercy on him, said, \u201cIf Allah wills good for a servant, He appoints a preacher from his heart to command and prohibit him.\u201d Source: al-Zuhd li-Ah\u0323mad ibn H\u0323anbal 1768 \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u062d\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a\u0628\u064d \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0650 \u0627\u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0633\u0650\u064a\u0631\u0650\u064a\u0646\u064e \u0631\u064e\u062d\u0650\u0645\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u064f \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0625\u0650\u0630\u064e\u0627 \u0623\u064e\u0631\u064e\u0627\u062f\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u064f \u0628\u0650\u0639\u064e\u0628\u0652\u062f\u064d \u062e\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0631\u064b\u0627 \u062c\u064e\u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":19264,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2014\/06\/03\/ibn-masud-enjoin-good-heart\/","url_meta":{"origin":39789,"position":2},"title":"Ibn Mas&#8217;ud on Conscience: He is ruined if he does not recognize good","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"June 3, 2014","format":false,"excerpt":"Tariq ibn Shihab reported: 'Itris ibn 'Urqub came to Abdullah ibn Mas\u2019ud, may Allah be pleased with him, and he said, \u201cHe is ruined who does not enjoin good and forbid evil.\u201d Abdullah said, \u201cRather, he is ruined who does not recognize good in his heart and reject evil in\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":27379,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/04\/03\/conscience-sin-agitates-heart\/","url_meta":{"origin":39789,"position":3},"title":"Ibn Mas\u2019ud on Conscience: Sin agitates the heart and mind","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"April 3, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Hannad ibn al-Sari reported: Ibn Mas'ud, may Allah be pleased with him, said, \"Sin is disturbing to the heart. There is never a glimpse of it but that Satan has ambition for it.\" Source: al-Zuhd li-Hanna\u0304d 935 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Al-Albani \u0639\u0646 \u0647\u0646\u0627\u062f \u0628\u0646 \u0627\u0644\u0633\u0631\u064a \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0627\u0628\u0652\u0646\u064f \u0645\u064e\u0633\u0652\u0639\u064f\u0648\u062f\u064d\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/faith-iman\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":11828,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/01\/25\/iman-leave-sins-heart\/","url_meta":{"origin":39789,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Conscience: Leave sins that shake your soul","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"January 25, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Umamah reported: A man asked the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, \u201cWhat is faith?\u201d The Prophet said, \u201cIf you are happy with your good deeds and saddened by your bad deeds, you are a believer.\u201d The man said, \u201cO Messenger of Allah, what is sin?\u201d\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/faith-iman\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":22796,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2016\/04\/30\/sin-disturb-conscience-heart-fatwa\/","url_meta":{"origin":39789,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Conscience: Sin shakes your heart, even if scholars approve","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"April 30, 2016","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Tha\u2019laba reported: I said, \u201cO Messenger of Allah, tell me what is lawful and unlawful for me.\u201d The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cRighteousness is serenity in the soul and peace of mind in the heart. Sin is not serene in the soul and not satisfying\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/39789","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/3712"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=39789"}],"version-history":[{"count":0,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/39789\/revisions"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=39789"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=39789"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/tags?post=39789"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}